infinite series and analytic functions can be simply and conveniently =
manipulated in categories of coalgebras. their taylor and laplace =
transforms turn up as coalgebra isomorphims. the basics of this approach =
are in my LICS 98 paper with martin escardo,
http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/mostRecentIssue.jsp?punumber=3D5684#
or
http://www.isg.rhul.ac.uk/dusko/coalgebra.html
neither martin nor i really pursued this path, which is perhaps a =
mistake, since it seems that a powerful categorical tool lies there.

2c,
-- dusko

